        "-200": "Rome's victory in the Second Punic War brings legions to Iberia, beginning two centuries of conquest as Celtiberian tribes wage desperate resistance—Numantia's siege epitomizing indigenous defiance crushed by Roman persistence—while coastal regions Romanize more quickly, Latin replacing Iberian scripts and Roman law superseding tribal customs, the peninsula's silver and grain flowing to Rome while its populations slowly, bloodily, integrate into the expanding Republic turned Empire.",
