        "100": "Roman Hispania reaches its zenith as the province's olive oil dominates Mediterranean markets, its cities adorned with monumental architecture, and its aristocrats send sons to study rhetoric in Rome, Christianity begins spreading through urban Jewish communities while traditional Roman and Celtic polytheism remain strong, the peninsula's integration into the empire so complete that its provincial origins matter little in an empire increasingly drawing talent from outside Italy, the Antonine dynasty continuing Hispania's contributions to imperial governance.",
