        "-100": "Italy suffers through Rome's civil wars as Marius and Sulla, Caesar and Pompey wage conflicts across the peninsula, proscriptions and confiscations devastating Italian communities while enriching opportunistic generals and their supporters, yet economic integration accelerates as Roman roads connect the peninsula and Italian agriculture shifts toward slave-plantation production of wine and olive oil for Mediterranean trade, citizenship now universal among free Italians, regional identities fading as Roman culture achieves hegemony.",
